                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Nov 66</cell>
                            <cell role="num">50,121</cell>
                            <cell role="num">48,704</cell>
                            <cell role="num">43,748</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    <p>2. Projection for December 1966 from Department of the Army is:</p>
                    <p>Assigned—51,800</p>
                    <p>On-Ground—49,000</p>
                    <p>Department of the Army has given no projections for strength beyond December
                        1966; however, it is assumed that Eighth US Army will be maintained at
                        approximately 51,000 assigned during the period January–June 1967.</p>
                </frus:attachment>
